{
  "text": "In the present study, patients who were treated for intestinal parasites had non-significant deterioration in urgency of defecation, blood in stool, general well being and extracolonic features compared to their baseline data. Buning et al. [CITATION_1] ; reported significant bleeding per rectum in their case report, a condition that was not encountered in the present study. This may be attributed to the short duration of follow up in the current study; (one month versus 6 months in their case).",
